---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Now | Tsung-Huan Yang" description="Current work and current curiosities">
  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Now</p>
    <h1>What I am focused on at the moment.</h1>
    <p class="lede">This page is meant to change often. It sits between a homepage intro, a research profile, and a personal log of what currently matters.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="split-grid">
    <article class="panel-card">
      <h2>Research</h2>
      <ul class="clean-list">
        <li>Safety evaluation and mitigation for fine-tuned language models</li>
        <li>Mechanistic interpretability and deceptive alignment questions</li>
        <li>Automated and multimodal red-teaming for language models</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
    <article class="panel-card">
      <h2>Current state</h2>
      <ul class="clean-list">
        <li>Preparing to start the MSCS program at Georgia Tech</li>
        <li>Expanding this site into a space for notes, case studies, and media tracking</li>
        <li>Trying to write more frequently without waiting for everything to feel polished</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="section-block">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Self-intro</p>
      <h2>Shorter and more personal than the homepage bio.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="prose-block">
      <p>
        I like research problems that are concrete enough to test but open-ended enough to keep revealing better
        questions. Most of my recent work has been around language models, multimodal systems, and safety evaluation.
      </p>
      <p>
        I also care a lot about how technical work is presented. Part of the reason for rebuilding this site is to
        make room for clearer writing, more visual project pages, and a less compressed version of what I am actually
        interested in.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="split-grid">
    <article class="panel-card">
      <h2>Reading and watching</h2>
      <ul class="clean-list">
        <li>Research that sharpens model evaluation rather than only leaderboard performance</li>
        <li>Design references with stronger framing, tension, and contrast</li>
        <li>Anime and films that feel clean-cut, bold, and slightly dangerous in composition</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
    <article class="panel-card">
      <h2>Site direction</h2>
      <ul class="clean-list">
        <li>Projects as dedicated full pages rather than modals</li>
        <li>Writing templates that support both quick notes and LaTeX-heavy posts</li>
        <li>A shelf page that reflects taste without swallowing the whole site</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
